# Ninja Agents

AI agents for engineering teams. Each agent is self-contained under `agents/`. Full workflow specs live in `.claude/agents/{name}.md`.

## Workflows

Invoke by name or describe what you need. Each rule in `.cursor/rules/` points to its full spec.

| Workflow | Description |
| -------- | ----------- |
| `@weekly-team-update` | Weekly team report for leadership |
| `@sprint-review` | Sprint retrospective analysis |
| `@sprint-planning-analysis` | Sprint planning health-check |
| `@repo-contextification` | Audit repo docs and AI-readiness |
| `@jira-qe-story` | Generate QE story from dev Jira story |
| `@jira-sprint-tickets-updater` | Transition sprint tickets based on linked PR status |

## Key Rules

- GitLab queries MUST include `scope: "all"` or results may be empty
- Only `resolution = "Done"` counts as a completed Jira deliverable
- CSV fields with commas must be double-quoted; report links use markdown hyperlinks
- Never commit tokens or secrets — env vars only (`GITHUB_PAT`, `GITLAB_PAT`)

